<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique Approves $111m Investment in 5 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique has approved 71 projects
with a total investment of 111 million U.S. dollars from January
to mid-May, the Mozambican Investment Promotion Center announced
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the investment, 10 million dollars come from domestic
investors, over 20 million dollars are foreign investment, and the
rest are loans, the investment center said.
</P>
<P>
Industrial sector has attracted 36.81 million dollars, while
agriculture and agro-industrial sector got 30,06 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The financial sector attracted 10 million, while tourism and
the hotel sector won 4.7 million, the investment center said.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique approved 202 projects with a total investment of 837
million dollars last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
