<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece Warns Turkey Over Trial of PKK Leader Ocalan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Greece warned Wednesday that Turkey
might try to use the trial of the Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK)
leader Abdullah Ocalan to influence Athens' domestic developments.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press briefing, Greek government spokesman
Dimitris Reppas said that it was certain that the neighboring
country would direct its arrows against Greece in light of a
possible verdict before the European Parliament elections on June
13.
</P>
<P>
Greece would confront every attempt by Turkey to influence
domestic developments in Greece, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan, who was arrested by Turkey in February, will be tried
Monday in a special state security court set up on the prison
island of Imrali off Istanbul on charges of treason. 
</P>
</TEXT>
