<DOCNO> XIE19990527.0004 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 19:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Concludes Visit to Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALEXANDRIA, Egypt, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese leader Li Ruihuan
left here on Wednesday for Beijing after winding up his first
official visit to Egypt.
</P>
<P>
During the six-day visit, Li, Chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, met with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and Prime
Minister Kamal El-Ganzouri.
</P>
<P>
He also held talks with Speaker of the Egyptian People's
Assembly, or parliament, Ahmed Fathi Sorour and Speaker of the
Egyptian Shura (Consultative) Council Mustafa Kamal Helmy.
</P>
<P>
During these meetings and talks, Li said China and Egypt have
established sincere and solid friendship and carried out close
cooperation since the two countries set up diplomatic ties in 1956.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Egyptian relations have withstood constant changes in
the international arena, Li said, adding Beijing and Cairo have
offered support and cooperation to each other in tackling
international issues.
</P>
<P>
On the economic globalization, Li called on the developing
countries to grasp every opportunity to develop themselves in the
process. Meanwhile, he cautioned that these countries should
select their development roads in conformity with reality.
</P>
<P>
Li also urged the developing countries to strengthen
cooperation in an effort to promote the establishment of a just
and new world order of politics and economy.
</P>
<P>
On the Middle East peace process, the Chinese leader called on
Israel to abide by the relevant U.N. resolutions and the
land-for-peace principle in a bid to push the peace process
forward.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian leaders shared Li's views on bilateral ties and
the international political and economic issues. They voiced
Egypt's readiness to work with China to boost such ties to a new
level.
</P>
<P>
Before his visit to Egypt, the Chinese leader has traveled to
South Korea, the United Arab Emirates and Oman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
