BAGHDAD -- The Iraqi government has agreed to renew the
oil-for-food program for another six months, or the sixth phase,
well-informed sources told Xinhua on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said on conditions of anonymity that Iraq had
agreed officially to extend the oil-for-food program for another
six months, adding that Iraq informed the U.N. of its decision on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi government has not formally announced its acceptance
of the extension of the oil-for-food program.
(BC-Iraq-Oil-for-Food Program)
</P>
<P>
