<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Producer Inflation Drops in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 26 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's year-on-year
producer inflation dropped to 4,9 percent in April, 0,6 percentage
points lower than in the previous month when the annual rate of
increase was 5,5 percent, Statistics South Africa said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The annual increase of 4,9 percent in the producer price index
(PPI) was due to annual increases in the price indices for locally
produced commodities (3,6 percent) and imported commodities (1,3
percent). 
</P>
</TEXT>
