<HEADLINE> Chinese Official Stresses Equality and Mutual </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 26 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese trade negotiator
said here on Wednesday that equality and mutual benefit are the
principle for world trade and China's guideline when negotiating
terms for its entry into the World Trade Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
Long Yongtu, the vice minister of the Ministry of Exterior
Trade and Cooperation of China, made the statement at a forum on
global trade which was organized by the Organization for Economic
Cooperation and Development.
</P>
<P>
Long said that economic globalization has become an
irreversible trend of the world economy and that China will
actively participate in this process.
</P>
<P>
But he said that China's opening to outside world is based on
the principle of equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
On the question of China's efforts to enter the WTO, Long said
that China will not sacrifice its fundamental interests in
exchange for its entry into the world trade body.
</P>
<P>
"Only when China enters the WTO on the basis of equality and
mutual benefit with others, can both China and other countries of
the world benefit from it," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
