<HEADLINE> ASEAN, EU Sign Work Plan for Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) and the European Union (EU) signed a work plan
Wednesday to promote their cooperation, said a report issued by
the on-going ASEAN-EU Joint Cooperation Committee (JCC) meeting.
</P>
<P>
Heads of delegations of both groupings signed the "New Dynamics
in EU and ASEAN Relations" work plan on the third day of the JCC
meeting.
</P>
<P>
The plan, reviewed by a JCC sub-committee Tuesday, will serve
as a blueprint for both regions for joint work in fields of civil
aviation, maritime cooperation, trade facilitation, transnational
crimes, forestry and business cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN-EU JCC meeting was resumed after a nearly two-year
break due to a diplomatic dispute over the presence of Myanmar,
which the EU claims is poor in human rights records.
</P>
<P>
However, after long negotiations, Myanmar has now been allowed
to attend the JCC meeting along with other new members of the
ASEAN, namely Laos and Cambodia, on the grounds that none of their
representatives speaks at the meeting. 
</P>
