<HEADLINE> Chinese Official: China to Further Expand Opening-Up Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- China will make its due
contributions to a prosperous world economy by further expanding
its reform and opening up drive, said a Chinese official at the
opening ceremony of the First Emerging Markets International Fair
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
China has been for five successive years ranking as the world's
second largest recipient of foreign investment, second only to the
United States, said Ma Xiuhong, Assistant Minister of the Ministry
of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"China will continue to better use more foreign investment, and
move actively towards integration with the world," she told the
participants from over 60 developing countries at the first-ever
international fair held mainly for emerging markets.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1998, Ma said, more than 324,000 foreign invested
enterprises have been set up in China, with paid-in foreign
investment standing at 267 billion U.S. dollars and foreign
investment sourced from over 170 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The international fair, supported by well-known organizations
like the United Nations Conference on Trade and Development, the
United Nations Industrial Development Organization and the World
Bank, will open until May 29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
