<HEADLINE> Karachi Stocks Plunge by 4.38 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Karachi stocks plunged by 4.38
percent Thursday amid heavy selling from all quarters owing to the
war-like situation between Pakistan and India in Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
The Karachi Stock Exchange (KSE) 100-share prices index fell
56.99 points to 1,243.71 from Wednesday's 1,300.7 points.
</P>
<P>
The trading volume stood at 192.416 million shares against
210.242 million shares a day ago.
</P>
<P>
Dealers are fearing that the country is heading toward war and
that will bring the economic revival to a standstill, analysts
said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 158 active issues, losers again outnumbered gainers 95
to 25 while 38 remained unchanged. 
</P>
