<DOCNO> XIE19990527.0051 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Turn Sci-Tech Research Institutes Into Enterprises (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- China is trying to turn its heavily
state-funded scientific and technological research institutes into
profit-making enterprises, Vice Premier Li Lanqing said here today.
</P>
<P>
"Helping sci-tech research institutes to become independent
enterprises based on science and technology, or research and
development departments affiliated with enterprises, will turn out
to be a major breakthrough in our country's reform of the existing
science and technology system," Li told a two-day forum on the
reform of sci-tech research institutes which ended in Beijing
today.
</P>
<P>
Jointly hosted by the Ministry of Science and the State
Economic and Trade Commission (SETC), the forum drew participants
from 242 sci-tech research institutes affiliated with 10 different
national administrative bureaus under the management of the SETC.
</P>
<P>
The 242 institutes, which will take the lead in introducing
major systematic shifts, can play a significant exemplary role in
the nationwide reform of the current science and technology system,
noted Li, also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
"Your separation from your former competent government
departments is also an experiment for the full-scale reform of
social institutions in the near future," said Li.
</P>
<P>
At the turn of the century, Li noted, the industrialization of
science and technology has become a distinct characteristic of
scientific and economic development worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said, a country's scientific and technological
power and its ability to turn this power into real productive
forces have become a factor which directly decides the country's
comprehensive national strength and international status, and has
a bearing on sovereignty and security.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, we must step up our efforts to implement our
strategy of reinvigorating China through science and education
with a strong sense of urgency and sense of crisis," he stressed.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990527.0052 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Turn Sci-Tech Research Institutes Into Enterprises (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Faced with the current global tide of economic and scientific
development, China has no other option but to prompt its sci-tech
research institutes to become enterprises, said the vice premier.
</P>
<P>
"Our ultimate purpose is not to diminish your research and
development capability, but to enhance it through adopting the new
system," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He also pledged that the state will increase its support for
sci-tech research, especially research on key technologies,
technologies that can be shared by an entire economic sector, and
high technologies of strategic importance.
</P>
<P>
"However, state funds for research programs will no longer be
allocated to you as in the past, and you must fight for it with
your actual strength and win it through opening bidding," said the
vice premier.
</P>
<P>
He urged all research institutes to try to establish, as
quickly as possible, a modern enterprise system with strict
management and good internal incentives once they have become
independent enterprises or part of an existing enterprise.
</P>
<P>
"Moreover, you must remember to seek survival and further
development through a constant improvement of your creativity and
scientific initiative, and always take it as your mission to
promote the development of our country's hi-tech sectors," he
suggested.
</P>
<P>
The vice premier also called on all relevant central government
departments and local governments across the country to give all-
out support to the reform of sci-tech research institutes.
</P>
<P>
Today's forum was presided over by Minister of Science Zhu
Lilan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
