<HEADLINE> '99 China Petroleum Conference Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The '99 China Petroleum Conference
opened here today with some 100 petroleum and natural gas experts
meeting to discuss oil industry restructuring, oil transportation,
and environmental issues related to oil exploration and production.
</P>
<P>
The conference, the fifth of its kind, is considered one of the
most important technical meetings of the petroleum industry.
</P>
<P>
Rob Lagaay, managing director of Asia Business Unit Chevron
Overseas Petroleum Inc., gave a keynote speech on the development
and utilization of natural gas resources in China.
</P>
<P>
Liu Wenlong, chief economist of China Petrochemical Corp.(
Sinopec), spoke of the challenges and opportunities Sinopec faces
after restructuring, and its long-term development strategy.
</P>
<P>
Discussing the topic "Facing the Challenges of the Market Today:
CNPC's Reinvention," Lu Yingjun, assistant president of China
National Petroleum Corporation (CNPC), briefed the conferees on
the newly organized CNPC's successful trial of lowering costs and
expanding market shares in the light of the over-supplied
international petroleum market. 
</P>
