<HEADLINE> Poll: Most Romanians Worried Over Lack of Dwellings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Most Romanians regard
insufficient dwellings as a problem that worries them most,
reported the official Rompres news agency Thursday.
</P>
<P>
89 percent of Romanians think the lack of dwellings is a
problem while 58 percent of the population view it as a grave
problem, the news agency quoted the result of an opinion poll
conducted by the Ministry of Public Works and Territorial Planning
as reporting.
</P>
<P>
Most Romanians think the best way to solve the problem is
providing people with loans with subsidized interest granted by
the state. 
</P>
