<HEADLINE> Vice Premier Attends Beijing Concert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Vice Premier Li Lanqing attended a
grand Chinese folk music concert here this evening marking this
year's 50th founding anniversary of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 students, former graduates, and young teachers
from 13 leading performing arts universities and colleges
performed at the concert tonight.
</P>
<P>
In 1949, China had only 18 performing arts schools with fewer
than 3,000 students. Now there are more than 160 performing arts
universities, colleges, and technical schools across the country
with some 100,000 students. These schools have trained a total of
more than 170,000 performing professionals over the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
Li, also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China Central Committee, enjoyed
the concert along with other senior government officials including
Minister of Culture Sun Jiazheng.  
</P>
</TEXT>
