<HEADLINE> Chinese Police Brings Back Embezzler from Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Public Security
disclosed today that police have brought back to China a criminal
suspect, accused of embezzling tens of millions of yuan of public
funds, from the Republic of Ecuador yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The 46-year-old Zhou Changqing, alias as Li Zhiming, was at
one time the general manager of the Mechanics and Electrical
Equipment Company of Shaanxi Province in northwest China.
</P>
<P>
During November and December of 1997, Zhou transferred more
than 40 million yuan and 26,000 U.S. dollars of public funds to a
company in the city of Zhuhai, a special economic zone in south
China.
</P>
<P>
After obtaining a visa for Ecuador illegally, Zhou fled to
that country in December 1997.
</P>
<P>
Chinese police discovered in March of 1999 that Zhou had
illicitly obtained a residence permit and citizenship in the
Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
The ministry immediately began to amass evidences against Zhou
and informed the police authorities in Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
Zhou was seized by police in Ecuador on May 11, and brought
back to China yesterday. The case is still under investigation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
