<DOCNO> XIE19990527.0062 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Meeting Calls for Regional Integration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 27 (Xinhua) -- ASEAN Chambers of Commerce and
Industry (CCI) Thursday called on the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN) to implement its action plan and the
measures proposed to promote regional integration to restore ASEAN
economic vitality.
</P>
<P>
In a joint press statement issued here at the end of its
three-day 56th Council Meeting, ASEAN CCI stressed the need for
the private sector to continue to be the engine of growth in the
region in order to ensure the success of the Hanoi Plan of Action
adopted at the ASEAN summit held in Hanoi last year.
</P>
<P>
The meeting reiterated the call on ASEAN governments to become
more market-driven and provide a business environment that
encourages entrepreneurship, more private ownership, consistent
policies and transparent regulations.
</P>
<P>
The existence of such conditions is essential to encouraging
intra-ASEAN cross-border investments which are the primary aim of
the Framework Agreement on the ASEAN Investment Area, the
statement added.
</P>
<P>
It stressed that the move toward achieving regional market
integration should not be hindered by inclination toward
protectionism. It added that the ASEAN Free Trade Area will enable
ASEAN to evolve into an integrated market of nearly half a billion
people and enhance the ability of the grouping to attract foreign
direct investment and promote restructuring of companies in the
region to meet global competition.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN should also expedite the elimination of non-tariff trade
barriers, it said.
</P>
<P>
The statement strongly encouraged the use of mutual recognition
arrangements to eliminate barriers arising from differences in
technical and quality standards.
</P>
<P>
The chambers voiced support for the candidacy of Supachai
Panichapat, deputy prime minister and minister of commerce of
Thailand, for the director-general of the World Trade
Organization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
