<HEADLINE> ASEAN, EU to Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) and the European Union (EU) agreed to strengthen
cooperation in trade and investment during their 13th Joint
Cooperation Committee (JCC) meeting, which ended here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Director-General of the Thai Foreign Ministry's Department of
ASEAN Affairs Anucha Osthanon said progress was also made on
narcotics and environmental cooperation.
</P>
<P>
A joint work program, called "New Dynamics in EU and ASEAN
Relations Work Plan," was signed during the meeting, which opened
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
EU's Emiliano Fossati, who co-chaired the ASEAN-EU JCC meeting
with Anucha, said the joint work plan would help strengthen
cooperation between the two regions in such areas as trade,
investment, tourism, intellectual property apart from that in
narcotics and environment fields.
</P>
<P>
The 13th ASEAN-EU JCC meeting was resumed after a nearly
two-year break due to a diplomatic dispute over the presence of
Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
The EU canceled earlier JCC meetings and a ministerial meeting
earlier this year in Berlin, saying Myanmar is poor in human
rights record.
</P>
<P>
So long as the EU sticks to its stance against Yangon, greater
cooperation between the two regions will be difficult, analysts
here said.
</P>
<P>
No date of the next ASEAN-EU JCC meeting and even the meetings
of the Sub-Committees on Narcotics and Environment was set during
the 13th JCC meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
