<HEADLINE> Building Of Long Three-Span Bridge Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a 6,426-meter-long
suspension bridge was completed today in the city of Xiamen in
east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The steel-box-girder Haicang Bridge has three spans and is the
largest of its kind ever built in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Its 1,108-meter-long main bridge has a span of 648 meters and
was built with the latest technology used for the first time for
bridge building in China.
</P>
<P>
Built at a cost of 2.874 billion yuan and with six-lanes, the
bridge is able to accommodate 5,000 vehicles a day.
</P>
<P>
The construction began 22 months ago.  
</P>
