<HEADLINE> Eritrea Claims 2,500 Ethiopian Soldiers Routed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian forces have been
fully dispersed in their attack against Eritrea launched on the
central flank of the Mereb-Setit front on May 25, said the
Eritrean Foreign Ministry in a press release reaching here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The release listed the Ethiopian losses in the fighting which
started May 21, claiming the Eritrean side "killed 785 Ethiopian
soldiers, wounded over 1,800 and captured 15."
</P>
<P>
"An Ethiopian helicopter gunship was shot down while large
quantities of medium and light weapons have been captured," the
Eritrean foreign ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Border fighting between the Horn of Africa neighbors resumed on
February 6 this year after a nine-month lull.
</P>
<P>
There are increasing calls from international and regional
communities for an immediate cessation of their hostilities. The
U.N. Security Council called for the full and immediate
implementation of its resolution on ceasefire in its session last
week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
