<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian President Benjamin
Mkapa Thursday condemned NATO's missiles attack on Chinese embassy
in Belgrade and expressed condolences to the families of the
victims.
</P>
<P>
In a message sent to Chinese President Jiang Zemin, Mkapa said,
" Tanzania strongly condemns this unacceptable incident and
appreciates the composure of the Chinese government
notwithstanding outrageous character of the attack."
</P>
<P>
Mkapa said he wished to convey the message of sympathy and
condolences to Jiang and to the government and people of China, on
behalf of the government and people of Tanzania and on his own
behalf.
</P>
<P>
