president said he shares the grief of the families of the three
people killed and more than 20 others wounded in the incident.
</P>
<P>
"I wish to join you, the government and the people of China in
consoling the bereaved and wishing the wounded a speedy recovery,"
Mkapa said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese embassy in Belgrade, Yugoslavia, was hit by five
missiles fired by the U.S.-led North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO) on the evening of May 7, in which three people were killed
and 20 others injured.
</P>
<P>
The Western alliance has been bombing Yugoslavia since March 24
in an attempt to force Belgrade to sign a peace agreement,
granting greater autonomy to the independence-seeking ethnic
Albanians in the Kosovo Province. 
