<HEADLINE> S.Korea Registered Trade Surplus of 2.5 Billion Dollars in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, May 27 (Xinhua) -- South Korea registered a trade
surplus of 2.5 billion U.S. dollars in April, said the Commerce,
Industry and Energy Ministry on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The surplus resulted from the export of 11.58 billion U.S.
dollars and the import of 9.08 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Last month, South Korea saw its export down 3.9 percent,
compared with the same month of last year. However, the import
rose 10.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the first four months of this year, South Korea's trade
surplus hit 7.26 billion U.S. dollars, with the export reaching 41.
91 billion U.S. dollars and the import 34.65 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
To seek an early economic recovery, South Korea has set its
export target at 40 billion U.S. dollars for this year. 
</P>
