<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province will
host the '99 China Small Commodity Goods Exposition from October 8-
12 in the city of Yiwu, the vice governor of the province Li
Changjiang told a news conference here today.
</P>
<P>
The yearly event is the fifth since 1995, and it has grown
into a large international fair providing opportunities for the
province to attract overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The exposition is jointly sponsored by the Zhejiang municipal
government, the State Administration of Light Industries, and the
State Administration of Internal Trade.
</P>
<P>
With over 26,000 booths, Yiwu, known as a City of Small
commodity in China, has led the country's 100,000 similar bazaars
in sales volume for eight straight years, with sales hitting 20
billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
the city has 4,300 trade markets with sales outlets in more
than 20 cities, provinces and autonomous regions in China and in
five countries and regions worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Last year's exposition concluded transactions involving 2.86
billion yuan and 694 enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Daily necessities, clothing, and non-staple food are the major
commodities to be displayed at the exposition.
</P>
<P>
A symposium on wholesale industrial products and a trade fair
will also take place during the expo. 
</P>
