<HEADLINE> China Improves Service for Small Businesses (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Small and medium-sized businesses account for 99.7 percent of
all industrial businesses in China, and employ 73 percent of the
industrial work-force. As jobs at state-owned companies had been
cut over the past few years, employment in the private sector grew
by 15 million people.
</P>
<P>
Wei said that along with improving training services for small
businesses, the government is working on favorable conditions to
finance them. The government will also issue directories of
products that it either encourages or discourages small
enterprises to produce.
