<HEADLINE> ASEAN Chambers of Commerce On Recovery From Economic Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 27 (Xinhua) -- ASEAN Chambers of Commerce and
Industry (CCI) Thursday called on both the private and public
sectors to learn from the regional economic crisis and restructure
to boost investor confidence for recovery from the crisis.
</P>
<P>
In a joint press statement issued here Thursday evening at the
end of the three-day 56th Council Meeting of CCI of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN), the chamber noted
that progress in reform has been made especially by the affected
countries.
</P>
<P>
The chamber recommends the adoption of measures to stimulate
demand in Asia as a main source of economic growth in addition to
export-led strategies to ensure a sustainable economic recovery.
</P>
<P>
The chamber warned against overborrowing and quick liquidation
of companies to ensure continued survival of viable ASEAN
corporations through sound corporate debt restructuring, improved
corporate governance and accountability.
</P>
<P>
The chamber stressed the development of an ASEAN bond market as
an alternative source of financing to avoid over-dependence on the
banking system for funds and to meet the financial needs of
long-term projects.
</P>
<P>
The chamber emphasized the need to learn from the current
crisis to exercise caution in their diversification strategy
especially into non-core businesses.
</P>
<P>
The chamber stressed the important role of small and
medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) in ASEAN economic recovery, saying
it will be implementing a program to assist SMEs in food
processing, handicrafts, garments, textiles and fashion apparel.
</P>
<P>
The chamber encouraged the ASEAN governments to ensure
long-term commitment to SMEs development and share successful
public and private sector experiences in SMEs development among
ASEAN countries.
</P>
<P>
The chamber also emphasized that any move to improve the global
financial system must begin with more transparency in currency
speculation and foreign exchange trading. 
</P>
</TEXT>
