<HEADLINE> K.P. Bhattarai Named New Prime Minister of Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Nepali King Birendra Thursday
appointed Nepali Congress senior leader Krishna Prasad Bhattarai
to head the first majority government in Nepal in four and half
years, a Royal Palace source said.
</P>
<P>
The appointment came as no surprise because Bhattarai was
offered the premiership months before the just-concluded elections
to the House of Representatives by Congress party president and
caretaker Prime Minister Girija Prasad Koirala.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali Congress won a majority of 110 seats in the
205-member House of Representatives. Bhattarai was elected earlier
the party's parliamentary party leader.
</P>
<P>
Under the kingdom's constitution, the king appoints the leader
of the parliamentary party having a majority in the house as the
prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Bhattarai, 75, has said his top priority will be poverty
eradication, followed by education and employment.
</P>
<P>
Bhattarai headed an interim government from April 1990 to May
1991 to draft a new constitution for the kingdom and hold the
first general elections after the multi-party parliamentary system
was restored in 1990.
</P>
<P>
Six governments had ruled the kingdom in the past four and half
a years after the mid-term polls in November 1994 produced a hung
parliament, where no single party commanded a majority. 
</P>
</TEXT>
