<HEADLINE> China Firm to Continue Reform, Opening Up (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The outrageous missile attack on
the Chinese embassy in Belgrade by the U.S.-led NATO should by no
means halt China's pace of reform and opening-up, but will only
serve to prompt the Chinese people to continue to advance this
great cause with stronger determination.
</P>
<P>
This statement is made in an editorial in the Friday edition of
the People's Daily, China's leading newspaper.
</P>
<P>
"The brutal atrocity of the U.S.-led NATO occurred at a time
when our country has achieved major breakthroughs in the reform
and opening-up drive and is assuming an increasingly important
role in the world arena," says the editorial, entitled "
Unswervingly Push the Reform and Opening Up."
</P>
<P>
Describing China's reform and opening-up policy as a "great
historical change," the editorial says that the policy has brought
fundamental changes to the destiny of both the Chinese nation and
socialism.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the reform and opening-up policy, it says, China's
social productive forces have been greatly emancipated and
developed over the past two decades, with the people's life and
the country's comprehensive national strength and international
status constantly improved.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, we must spare no effort to ensure the advancement
and final success of the reform and opening-up drive, and we can't
afford any setbacks or failure," it adds.
</P>
</TEXT>
