<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Firm to Continue Reform, Opening Up (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Since it is an "unprecedented" attempt in the world, says the
editorial, it is quite natural for China's reform and opening-up
efforts to meet difficulties and resistance, as well as various
disturbances and sabotage from hostile forces both inside and
outside China.
</P>
<P>
"However, there is no difficulty or circumstance that can sway
our determination and slow down our pace of reform and opening-up,
" it says.
</P>
<P>
The editorial goes on to say that China will continue to carry
out economic and technological exchanges and cooperation with
foreign countries, protect the legitimate rights and interests of
all overseas investors and business people according to law, and
further expand the scope of opening up to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
"This is conducive not only to China's own development, but
also to the development of all other countries, including
developed Western countries," it stresses.
</P>
<P>
While never allowing any other countries to infringe upon
China's sovereignty and dignity with any excuses, the editorial
says, the Chinese government and people are willing to develop
friendly relations and seek common development with the rest of
the world on the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful Co-
existence.
</P>
<P>
"Our reform and opening-up drive has a promising future and we
will have friends all over the world," concludes the editorial.
</P>
