<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese border police in Fuzhou,
capital of the coastal province of Fujian in southeast China, on
Wednesday morning intercepted at sea 90 Chinese citizens
attempting to sneak into the United States by taking a boat from
the Republic of Korea (ROK), local authorities announced today.
</P>
<P>
The police also arrested 17 "snakeheads," or organizers of the
illegal immigration, including four ROK nationals.
</P>
<P>
