<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The Publicity Department of the
Communist Party of China Central Committee and the Ministry of
Personnel today jointly granted the title of "outstanding
journalist" to the three Chinese reporters killed in the U.S.-led
NATO missile attack on the Chinese embassy in Belgrade early this
month.
</P>
<P>
The three, Shao Yunhuan of the Xinhua News Agency, and Xu
Xinghu and Zhu Ying of the Beijing-based Guangming Daily, had
earlier been honored with the title of "revolutionary martyr" by
the Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
The seven other honored journalists, who remain in Yugoslavia,
work for Xinhua, the People's Daily, China Central Television (
CCTV), and China Radio International (CRI).
</P>
<P>
The CPC top publicity organ and the personnel ministry also
bestowed the honor of first-class merit on eight other Chinese
correspondents in Yugoslavia who are employed by Xinhua, CCTV, and
CRI.
</P>
<P>
"These honored are outstanding representatives of Chinese
journalism, as well as the pride of the entire Chinese nation,"
said a written citation jointly issued by the publicity department
and the personnel ministry to news media around the country.
</P>
<P>
All Chinese journalists should learn from the 18 honored
journalists, show loyalty to the Party's journalistic undertakings,
put the motherland's interests higher than anything else, dedicate
themselves to their career and duty, and always face up to any
difficulties, the citation urged. 
</P>
