<HEADLINE> Northwest Region to Stage Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region is to stage the '99 Urumqi Foreign Economic Relations and
Trade Fair between September 1-8, in the regional capital of
Urumqi, the region's vice-chairman Zhang Zhou told a news
conference here today.
</P>
<P>
The yearly event is the eighth since 1992, growing into the
largest international trade fair of its kind in the west of China
and has become known as a showcase for the country to open
westward.
</P>
<P>
The former seven fairs attracted more than 18,000 business
people from across 73 countries and regions, with 180 foreign
enterprises participating in exhibitions. Some 7.6 billion U.S.
dollars worth of contracts have been signed over the years.
</P>
<P>
The ethnic region has established trade relations with 83
countries and regions, and had 1.5 billion U.S. dollars worth of
imports and exports last year. And by last year it had used 2.2
billion U.S. dollars of investment in real terms.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang, in the hinterland of Asia and Europe, borders on
eight countries, with the second Eurasian Continental Bridge
running across it. It also has 15 entry and exit ports and is rich
in natural resources, especially oil and minerals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
