<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Firmer on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Share prices gyrated from
negative to positive territory on Singapore Stock Market Thursday
buoyed by bargain hunting and overnight rally on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index gained 22.04 points to end at
1,915.77 points, staying above the 1,900 level after an active
session.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover expanded to 1,569.65 million shares worth
1,376.02 million Singapore dollars (795.89 million U.S. dollars).
Advancers edged out decliners by 223 to 117 with 104 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Econ Int was the top active mover of the day as it registered a
turnover of 56.55 million shares. It was followed by Lian Beng
which had 44.50 million shares done. AFP, the Indonesia-linked
Asia Food and Property, was the next with 40.16 million counters
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
CityDev, the property heavyweight, was the biggest gainer of
the day with a run-up of 75 cents to 10.40 Singapore dollars.
Creative 50, NatElec and UOB F climbed up 60 cents each to close
at 22.80, 5.85 and 11.90 Singapore dollars respectively. Bukit Sem
picked up 40 cents to end at 19.50 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, OUB F headed the descent of the day with a
loss of 35 cents to close at 9.20 Singapore dollars. Thai Pr shed
25 cents to finish at 5.50 U.S. dollars. OCBC F, SPH and SPH 100
retreated 20 cents each to end at 13.60, 24.00, and 24.00
Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said prices closed firmer on bargain-hunting after
recent weakness.
</P>
<P>
They also said the overnight advance on Wall Street also helped
spur sentiment in the local market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
