<DOCNO> XIE19990527.0168 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 08:50 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 54 U.S. Warplanes to be deployed in Two Turkish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 27 (Xinhua) -- A Turkish military chief has said
that 54 U.S. warplanes will be deployed at two military bases in
in western Turkey in early June as part of the expanded air
attacks against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Local Millilyet (National) daily Thursday quoted Turkish
General Staff Chief Huseyin Kivrikoglu as saying that 36 fighter
jets would be deployed at the air base in Balikesir and the other
18 warplanes would be deployed at the air base in Bandirma.
</P>
<P>
Kivrikoglu added that negotiations are continuing between
Turkish and NATO officials on determining the base where tanker
planes to be deployed.
</P>
<P>
The North Atlantic Treaty Organization decided to deploy 72
fighter jets, including 18 Turkish warplanes at three Turkish
military bases for its air campaign against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The United States-led western military bloc is expected to
launch attacks on targets in Yugoslavia from Turkey via an air
corridor over Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, local Hurriyet (Freedom) daily reported that the
first U.S. experts team had arrived at the military base in
Balikesir last week for technical infrastructure works.
</P>
<P>
A total of 4,000 U.S. personnel will soon arrive at the two
military bases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
