<HEADLINE> China Speeds Up Credit Guarantee System for Small Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government is expected
to speed up its newly developed credit guarantee system for medium-
and small-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Shao Ning, director general of the Enterprise Reform Department
of the State Economic and Trade Commission (SETC), said here today
that this is part of China's efforts to create a comprehensive
support system for the sectors in a bid to boost the economy.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the "Top Management Day" hosted by the Swedish
Chamber of Commerce in China, Shao said that the SETC is drawing
up policies to facilitate the development of medium- and small-
sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"Other support systems are also under way in areas such as
technological innovation, training, and information and management
consultancy services," Shao said.
</P>
<P>
China's medium- and small-sized enterprises have low credit
levels in banks and thus find themselves hard pushed to secure
loans or mortgages.
</P>
<P>
The credit guarantee system will provide a strong support to
those enterprises, with contributions from the Ministry of Finance
and local financial sectors.
</P>
<P>
A guarantee fund in this respect started operation in February
in Zhenjiang of east China's Jiangsu province.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-nine small enterprises in Shanghai, China's top
industrial and commercial center, have been granted 60.5 million
yuan of loans as part of the measures the city is taking to
support and promote the sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
