<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique's Opposition Party to Hold Congress in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The Mozambican Resistance Movement
(RENAMO), the biggest opposition party of the country, decided to
hold its fourth congress from July 26 to 29.
</P>
<P>
RENAMO President Afonso Dhlakama made the announcement in
Maputo Wednesday at close of the meeting of RENAMO national
committee which was a preparatory for the congress.
</P>
<P>
The Noticias newspaper quoted Dhlakama as saying that the
congress will be the first meeting of the party after peace was
achieved in the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Dhlakama will be nominated as the party's
presidential candidate to run for the presidency with current
President Joaquim Chissano who is also the chairman of the ruling
Mozambique Liberation Front Party.
</P>
<P>
At the fourth congress of the RENAMO, the party constitution
and program will be re-written because the old ones had been
adopted in the warring period.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the coming second multi-party election, Dhlakama
noted that his party insists that the election be held this year.
</P>
<P>
But if the parties reach agreement on its postponement, he
said, the general election may be put off until next year.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the activities of illegal militiamen in northern and
central provinces, Dhlakama pointed out that his party loves peace
and comply with the international principles, denying any relation
with these activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
