<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Registration Rules on Adoption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- New registration rules on the
adoption of Chinese children by foreigners and Chinese citizens
have been introduced by China's Ministry of Civil Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners who want to adopt Chinese children must now come to
China themselves to register. If one of a couple can not come, he
or she must provide a written and notarized letter.
</P>
<P>
They also have to provide notarized information on their
background, age, marital status, occupation, property, health and
police record. Their adoption relationship will go into effect
right after the registration.
</P>
<P>
Also the new regulation stops the charging of fees but
encourages adopters to donate funds to orphanages.
</P>
<P>
Chinese people are now allowed, regardless of whether they have
children or not, to adopt more than one orphan. But according to
the new regulation, Chinese citizens who want to adopt children in
every case should register at civil affairs departments.
</P>
<P>
The new rules also provide directions on the adoption of
Chinese children by Chinese citizens living in Hong Kong, Macao
and Taiwan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
