<HEADLINE> U.S. Urged to Eliminate Odious Influence of Cox's Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The charges against China in
Christopher Cox's report are absolutely lies based on fabrication,
said Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao at a press conference
here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said the charges are made for certain political motives and
they are aimed at defaming China, inciting anti-China mood and
undermining Sino-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
He said, "We urge the U.S. administration to firmly oppose it,
and take effective measures to eliminate its odious influence."
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that China has never stolen nuclear technologies
or secrets from any countries, including the United States.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he pointed out that the United States has powerful
spy and intelligence institutes, from which scandals have been
exposed. "These institutes have never stopped espionage in other
countries."
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government is also firmly opposed to any espionage
against China," Zhu stated.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that China is a peace advocate and
responsible country, which abides by the U.N. Charter and acts in
line with international laws and norms. 
</P>
