<HEADLINE> Australia's Richest Man 792 Million U.S. Dollars Richer in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Australia's richest man Kerry
Packer just kept getting richer in 1998, adding a tidy 1.2
billion Australian dollars (792 million U.S. dollars) to his
fortune.
</P>
<P>
The rise of the Australian stock market over the last 12 months
saw the media tycoon expand his total wealth to 4.2 billion U.S.
dollars, according to the Business Review Weekly magazine's Rich
200 list to be released Friday.
</P>
<P>
This translates to 2.1 million U.S. dollars a day.
</P>
<P>
His nearest rival is Westfield shopping center boss, Frank
Lowy, at 1.71 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Packer's performance has largely been based on the strength of
his stake in the listed magazine and television empire, Publishing
and Broadcasting Ltd. 
