<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Tops List of Kenyan Tea Buyers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan has overtaken the United
Kingdom as the number one importer of Kenyan tea with the import
of 14.4 million kilograms worth 1.7 billion shillings (about 26
million U.S. dollars) in January and February this year.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics released by the African Tea Brokers
Limited, the U.K. imported 11.7 million kilograms valued at about
21.5 million dollars during the same period, the Daily Nation
newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
During the period, Kenya sold some 45.6 million kilograms of
tea worth about 80 million dollars to 39 countries represented at
the Mombasa auction.
</P>
<P>
According to the figures released by the African Tea Brokers,
Egypt ranked the third having bought nine billion kilograms worth
some 15 million dollars while Afghanistan was the fourth with the
import of 2.4 million kilograms valued at 3.7 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, Kenya exported a total of 264,200 tons of tea to 40
countries and earned 580 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
