<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Passenger Arrivals to Macao Increase in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Passenger arrivals to Macao by means
of marine, land and air routes totaled 706,421 in April, an
increase of 8.7 percent over the same month of 1998, latest
official statistics show.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released Thursday by the Macao Census and
Statistics Department, the number of passengers to Macao in the
first four months of this year rose 1.7 percent over the January-
April period of last year.
</P>
<P>
During the four months, passengers coming from Hong Kong
accounted for 61 percent of the total. In comparison with the same
period of 1998, however, passenger arrivals from Hong Kong
decreased 16.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, passenger arrivals from the inland areas of
China, the Republic of Korea and South Asian countries increased
134.5 percent, 66 percent and 53.5 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, annual passenger arrivals to Macao
were around seven million. In 1998, the figure was 6,948,535.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990527.0212 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ugandan Top Police Officer Accused of Embezzlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 27 (Xinhua) -- A top Ugandan police officer on
forced leave has been accused of diverting police welfare money to
do his own business.
</P>
<P>
Chris Bakiza, director of the country's Criminal Investigation
Department (CID), is said to have diverted the money to his
company which supplies ceremonial uniforms to the force, the New
Vision daily reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The company, Brevans Enterprises Limited, is run by his wife,
daughter and son, the report added.
</P>
<P>
A witness was quoted as saying that Bakiza had threatened him
with death when he demanded that Bakiza pay back the 19 million
shillings (150,000 U.S. dollars) he lent him to replace the
diverted fund.
</P>
<P>
It was the officer's wife who came to borrow the money because
the officer himself did not want his movements to be monitored by
auditors monitoring him.
</P>
<P>
Bakiza is the second senior police officer charged with using
the force' s money to make personal profits.
</P>
<P>
Former police boss John Odomel faced the same charges last year
and was forced to resign on January 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
The three-man inquiry team responsible for the probe into
Bakiza's case has just been formed by the Ministry of Internal
Affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990527.0213 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi's Largest Privately-Funded Power Station Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- One of the largest hydropower
stations in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region funded
by a private enterprise has come on stream in Tiandong County.
</P>
<P>
Costing 43-million yuan the Denggao Power Station has three
generating units of 25 million kilowatt hours (kwh) each and a
designed generating capacity of 43 million kwh a year. It is
expected to help ease the county's energy shortage.
</P>
<P>
According to the county government office, the station has been
funded by farmer-turned entrepreneur Ban Guangxi, who owns the
Guangxi Denggao Group with total assets of 120 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Ban has also invested 45 million yuan on building another
hydropower station which is expected to be completed by the end of
next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990527.0214 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Civil Dispute Mediators Urged to Play Greater Role in Maintaining Stability in China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Minister of Justice Gao
Changli has called on the country's 10 million civil dispute
mediators to play a greater role in dissolving the "internal
contradictions of the people" to help maintain social stability.
</P>
<P>
"China faces many difficulties and problems at this crucial
time of reform and development, and the characteristics of the
large number of civil disputes today are quite different from
before," he said at a national conference on mediation work.
</P>
<P>
Known as "the people's mediators," those elected neighborhood
peacemakers are an important part of the country's legal system,
since they prevent hundreds of thousands of quarrels from flaring
up into criminal offenses every year.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics from the Ministry of Justice, there are
9.175 million members in 985,000 "people's mediators committees"
spread through every corner of society.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990527.0215 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
