<DOCNO> XIE19990527.0218 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Expert Suggests Widening Channel for Non-State Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- An expert from the National Bureau
of Statistics today suggested that the Chinese government actively
develop non-state financial institutes to widen the channel for
non-state investment.
</P>
<P>
The investment by the non-state sector witnessed a growth of 8.
6 percent and eight percent in 1997 and 1998 respectively, but
these figures are 0.4 and 11.6 percentage points lower than the
state sector in the same period.
</P>
<P>
The expert blamed the slow development of the non-state
financial institutes, yet in comparison the non-state firms
themselves have enjoyed rapid development in the past years.
</P>
<P>
He recommended that the government should not simply close or
merge those institutes which are involved in illegal operations or
facing a payment crisis, but should guide them to develop while
strengthening supervision of them.
</P>
<P>
He also suggested the government set up national or regional
funds to back the development of small and medium-size non-state
firms.
</P>
<P>
"Large commercial banks should also provide more support in
this area," he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that to enliven non-state investment, the government
should also simplify the approval procedure and let investments
flow into more fields.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990527.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ningxia's Commodity Exhibition Center Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, May 27 (Xinhua) -- A commodity exhibition center
opened in this capital of northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region.
</P>
<P>
Exhibits at the center, the largest of its kind in Ningxia,
covered the sectors of machinery and electronics, metallurgy, coal,
chemical products, medicine, light industry, agriculture and
tourism. Visitors also had the opportunity to appreciate Ningxia's
natural scenery and folklore.
</P>
<P>
More than 180 enterprises in the region attended an show held
in the center today, which exhibits more than 600 varieties of
products.
</P>
<P>
The Ningxia Commodity Exhibition Center was built a short time
ago and covers more than 1,800 square meters. Local authorities
said that it offers a window for Ningxia to show the "fruits" of
its opening-up and carry out international business cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia has set up business links with more than 70 countries
and regions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
