<HEADLINE> Civil Dispute Mediators Urged to Play Greater Role in Maintaining Stability in China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Minister of Justice Gao
Changli has called on the country's one million civil dispute
mediators to play a greater role in dissolving the "internal
contradictions of the people" to help maintain social stability.
</P>
<P>
"China faces many difficulties and problems at this crucial
time of reform and development, and the characteristics of the
large number of civil disputes today are quite different from
before," he said at a national conference on mediation work.
</P>
<P>
Known as "the people's mediators," those elected neighborhood
peacemakers are an important part of the country's legal system,
since they prevent hundreds of thousands of quarrels from flaring
up into criminal offenses every year.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics from the Ministry of Justice, there are
9.175 million members in 985,000 "people's mediators committees"
spread through every corner of society.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990527.0233 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Civil Dispute Mediators Urged to Play Greater Role in Maintaining Stability in China (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"They handled 87,000 civil disputes in 1998, stopped 36,000
armed fights amongst groups and helped to keep another 36,000
groups of complainants from taking to the streets ," the minister
said.
</P>
<P>
And in the past twenty years the people's mediators handled 127.
86 million civil cases, 5.3 times more than the country's courts,
prevented 1.503 million attempted suicides triggered by civil
disputes, and halted 135.8 million quarrels from escalating into
crimes.
</P>
<P>
The minister said, however, that much more needs to be done to
cope with the rising number of conflicts as a result of the
exorbitant burden on farmers, the layoffs from loss-making state-
owned enterprises and irregularities in the relocation of
residents in urban construction.
</P>
<P>
He called on mediation committees across the country to study
the process of how disputes arise and their escalation and
explosion into crises, and to try all means to solve the feuds
before they become too acute.
</P>
<P>
In particular, he encouraged the setup of more hot lines and
mediation centers in neighborhoods and especially in large and
medium-sized state-owned enterprises as part of crisis-control
efforts.
</P>
<P>
In addition to democratic elections, China is also trying to
take steps in hiring lawyers to also serve as pacifiers, according
to the minister.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
