<HEADLINE> Supreme Procuratorate Orders Earnest Handling of Appeals of HK, Taiwan, Macao Residents, Overseas Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The Supreme People's Procuratorate
(SPP) issued a circular today, ordering all prosecution officials
to "earnestly and responsibly" handle reports, lawsuits and
appeals by residents of Hong Kong, Taiwan, Macao and overseas
Chinese, a SPP spokesman said here today.
</P>
<P>
"Such a move is to faithfully ensure the legitimate rights of
their rights and interests," he added.
</P>
<P>
The circular said that these matters must be treated earnestly
and responsibly, and their calls and visits should be received
with appropriate courtesy.
</P>
<P>
If such cases are within the jurisdiction of the people's
procuratorates, they must be carefully reviewed and brought within
the legal procedure in time, with final results fedback also in
good in time, the circular said, noting that if the case is to be
rejected, the reporter, accuser or appeal maker must be informed
of the reason.
</P>
<P>
In another instance, if the reported case does fall not within
the prosecution office's areas responsibility, the office is
accountable for transferring it to relevant departments in proper
time, and let this be known to the crime reporter, accuser or
complainant.  
</P>
</TEXT>
