<HEADLINE> Palmeiras Edges River Plate 3-0 in Libertadores Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Alex netted two goals as Brazil's
Palmeiras defeated Argentina's River Plate 3-0 in Sao Paulo on
Wednesday night to advance to the Libertadores Cup final on 3-1
aggregate.
</P>
<P>
Alex scored the opening goal in the 17th minute on a feed from
Zinho. Roque Junior gave Palmeiras room to breath in the 19th
minute, heading it past River Plate goalkeeper Bonano.
</P>
<P>
Palmeiras easily dominated the field setting up attack after
attack only to blow it at the last minute, with the ball hitting
the post or being knocked wide by the goalkeeper.
</P>
<P>
All Palmeiras' efforts paid off in the 87th minute when Paulo
Nunes crossed it to Alex, who crossed it back and into the goal
high and to the right.
</P>
<P>
Palmeiras advanced to the final agaist Colombia's Deportivo
Cali, which defeated Paraguay's Cerro Porteno on 6-3 aggregate
after falling 3-2 on Wednesday night in Asuncion. 
</P>
