<HEADLINE> China's Pharmaceutical Industry Expected Better Climate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- China's pharmaceutical industry is
expecting a better climate in the second quarter of this year,
according to a recent survey.
</P>
<P>
Launched by the China Economic Climate Monitoring Center and
the State Economic and Trade Commission, the survey shows that the
indices of employees, raw material prices and products in storage
are going up.
</P>
<P>
The center analyzed that pharmaceutical firms are optimistic
about the sales volume and economic returns in the second quarter.
The survey show that 64 percent of firms surveyed said they expect
a larger sales volume in the April-June period.
</P>
<P>
But because the state's price-adjustment policy will be
published in the second quarter of this year, only four percent of
firms think that medicine prices will go up in the period.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter of this year, affected by the expected
medical system reform and the price-adjustment policy, the
pharmaceutical industry suffered a sluggish climate.  
</P>
</TEXT>
