<HEADLINE> SAFE Opens Website </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- China's State Administration of
Foreign Exchange (SAFE) announced today that it will officially
launch its website on May 28.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the SAFE said that the opening of the website
is an important step to increase the transparency and openness of
the country's foreign exchange administration, and to improve the
legal environment of foreign exchange administration.
</P>
<P>
Information on the SAFE's website mainly includes foreign
exchange news, an introduction to the SAFE, policies and
regulations, statistics, a business guide and consultation. The
contents will be frequently updated.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that through the website, the SAFE will
publish the latest information on foreign exchange administrative
policies and regulations, introduce the business procedures of
foreign exchange administrative departments, as well as
explanation of newly-issued laws and regulations.
</P>
<P>
He said that the SAFE expects to better communicate with the
social community and provide guidance for institutions and
individuals to do foreign exchange business.  
</P>
