<HEADLINE> "Global Democratization", Camouflage of U.S. Hegemony: Signed Article (8) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chinese people have long been familiar with this kind of
logic and sermonizing.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 years ago, when the imperialist powers entered
China with their advanced weapons and committed all kinds of
crimes, forcing the then weak and poor China to sign unequal
treaties and taking their shares of the Chinese territory and
possessions, they provided the pretext of "spreading Western
civilization" or helping establish "a paradise under benevolent
governments" in China.
</P>
<P>
Nowadays, while wantonly bombing the small and weak Yugoslavia,
the NATO member states are repeating the warlike tones of their
predecessors. The words and deeds of the hegemonists headed by the
United States are no more than updated versions of those advocated
by the old imperialists that aggression is reasonable and
meritorious, which represent power politics, the gunboat policy
and the logic of a thief.
</P>
<P>
However, the hegemonists today are much smarter than the
earlier ones. While inheriting the mantle of the old imperialists,
they are advocating a "new theory of interference" with some new
characteristics. They are no longer "fighting for land" because
the traditional gunboat policy of grabbing and sharing land has
become both unworkable and not worthwhile. In today's world, the
benefits of establishing an international political and economic
order conforming to the interests of the Western countries far
outweighs that of grabbing land because there are more choices and
more advanced ways of making a fortune.
</P>
</TEXT>
