<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: China's Exports in Terms of Different Ownership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Following are facts and figures
about China's exports in January-April of 1999 in terms of
different trade types and ownership, provided by the General
Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
Exports of general trade by state-owned businesses declined 20.
3 percent to 15.84 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Exports of general trade by overseas-funded businesses rose 13.
2 percent to 3.31 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Volume of processing and assembly exports with supplied
materials by state-owned businesses decreased 0.4 percent to 6.37
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Volume of processing and assembly exports with supplied
materials by overseas-funded businesses increased 41.9 percent to
reach 2.81 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Volume of processing exports with customers' materials by state-
owned businesses dropped 16.6 percent to 2.66 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Volume of processing exports with customers' materials by
overseas-funded businesses decreased 2.9 percent to 18.07 billion
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
