<HEADLINE> S.Korean President Begins Visit to Russia, Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, May 27 (Xinhua) -- South Korean President Kim Dae-jung
left here Thursday morning on official visits to Russia and
Mongolia in a move to further expand relations with the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
President Kim is expected to meet Russian and Mongolian leaders
to discuss economic cooperation and regional security.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean president is scheduled to meet his Russian
counterpart Boris Yeltsin to secure Russia's support for a peace
initiative on the Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
Moscow will voice its support of President Kim's "sunshine
policy" with Pyongyang, aimed at helping Pyongyang on the path of
reform and openness, said South Korean Unification Minister Lim
Dong-won.
</P>
<P>
Economic cooperation between South Korea and Russia is also
believed to be a focus of the summit and some agreements will be
signed.
</P>
<P>
A total of 80 South Korean business executives are accompanying
Kim to Russia and Mongolia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
