<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: China's Imports in Terms of Different Ownership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Following are facts and figures
about China's imports in January-April of 1999 in terms of
different trade types and ownership, provided by the General
Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
Imports of general trade by state-owned businesses increased by
70.4 percent to 14.27 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Imports by overseas-funded businesses jumped 92.3 percent to 4.
45 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Imports for processing and assembly with supplied materials by
state-owned businesses fell 5.4 percent to 4.17 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Imports for processing and assembly with supplied materials by
overseas-funded companies increased 34.3 percent to 1.85 billion
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Imports for processing with customers' materials by state-owned
businesses dropped 27.2 percent to 1.28 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Imports of processing with customer's materials by overseas-
funded businesses fell 3.9 percent to 12.82 billion dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
