<HEADLINE> IMF Delegation to Visit Brazil in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of the International
Monetary Fund will arrive in Brazil early next month to revise the
objectives of a previously agreed accord to enable Brazil to get
further IMF loans.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's Secretary of Economic Politics of the Finance Ministry
Edward Amadeo said the IMF delegation will check the goals to
which Brazil must adhere throughout the 3rd and 4th quarters of
the year.
</P>
<P>
He said there is a possibility that Brazil may not receive the
third part of an emergency loan if Brazil failed to get the
revision. "The decision, to eventually obtain the loan, depends
on the flow of capital and the level of international reserves in
the country."
</P>
<P>
Brazil's Central Bank reported that the country's foreign
exchange reserves until May 25 reached 44.62 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Brazil has received the first and second parts of the loan,
adding up to 18 billion U.S. dollars. The country is expecting
the third and fourth parts of the loan which in total will be 41.5
billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
