<HEADLINE> Southern City Becomes China's Largest Dye-Stuff Producer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The city of Maoming in China's
Guangdong Province has become China's largest producer of kaolin,
a dye-stuff for paper making, with proven reserves of 800 million
tons.
</P>
<P>
The city now produced 80 percent of the country's kaolin and
has dozens of enterprises engaged in kaolin work, with an annual
production capacity of 140,000 tons. In 1998, the city's output
value of kaolin was 300 million yuan and it has become one of the
city's major source of revenues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
