<HEADLINE> Austrian Chancellor: Austria Adheres to Neutrality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Austrian Federal Chancellor Viktor
Klima said Wednesday that Austria will neither join any military
alliances, get involve in wars, nor allow foreign military
presence in the country.
</P>
<P>
Klima reiterated his country's three principles of neutrality
at a press briefing held here after the Council of Ministers ended
its regular meeting.
</P>
<P>
To remain neutral or to join NATO and the European Union has
become a hot topic in Austria. The European Union is scheduled to
hold its summit next month, and the European Parliament will also
hold its general election next month.
</P>
<P>
Klima said that he believes the EU will not force its member to
join NATO.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the EU summit, to be held in Koln on June
13, would not adopt any resolution detrimental to Austria's
neutrality. 
</P>
</TEXT>
