<HEADLINE> Peruvian President Not to Attend Andean Presidential Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori
Wednesday canceled his trip to Colombia to attend the 11th Andean
Presidential Summit, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Victor Joy Ways has left for Colombia to replace
him, sources said.
</P>
<P>
They said Fujimori canceled the trip at the last moment because
he wanted to supervise the work after heavy rains hit Iquitos, a
city in Peru's northeast province of Loreto. But local reports say
Fujimori made the decision for security reasons.
</P>
<P>
The 11th Andean Presidential Summit, which opened on Wednesday,
will establish the basis for the planned Andean Common Market and
a common external political policy for the five member countries.
</P>
<P>
The Andean Community groups Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Peru
and Venezuela. 
