<HEADLINE> Argentina Sends First Balloon to Measure Ozone Over Antarctic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENAS AIRES, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Argentina's National
Directorship of the Antarctic on Wednesday launched the country's
first aerostatic balloon to measure the ozone layer and conditions,
from the General Belgrano base.
</P>
<P>
The launch was performed in cooperation with the Institute of
Aerospace Techniques of Spain, said the organization.
</P>
<P>
The sphere which has a diameter of 1.8 meters, will reach an
altitude of 30,000 meters to measure the ozone level in the
atmosphere and transmit valuable information back to the ground
base.
</P>
<P>
If this experiment is successful, Argentina plans to launch two
balloons every month in the future, and will launch two balloons
per week throughout September, as this is the time when the hole
in the ozone layer is more obvious, the local media reported.
</P>
</TEXT>
