<HEADLINE> Taiwan Businessmen Show Interest in Hainan's Real Estate Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Eighty-six senior executives from
Taiwan's real estate sector have visited Hainan Province in south
China recently and shown interest in developing the market in the
province.
</P>
<P>
At a real estate conference in Hainan, a senior official
briefed the businessmen the province's policy on the development
of the sector as well as its problem of slack sales.
</P>
<P>
Since Hainan Province was established 10 years ago, it has
completed construction of 11.58 million square meters of
commercial housing. However, less than half or 4.91 million square
meters of space has been sold.
</P>
<P>
This year, the central government has listed Hainan as an
experiment zone for tackling the problem of current vacant housing.
A detailed scheme is to be worked out by the province in line with
state preferential policies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
