<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Foreign Exchange Reserves Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's net foreign exchange
reserves increased to 15.98 billion U.S. dollars in the week
ending on May 21 from 15.92 billion dollars in the previous week,
the central bank said in its latest weekly report.
</P>
<P>
Bank Indonesia attributed the increase in the country's net
foreign exchange reserves to oil revenues.
</P>
<P>
The net international reserves were above the 15.4 billion
dollars target set by the International Monetary Fund.
</P>
<P>
Gross international reserves -- net foreign exchange reserves
plus outstanding foreign exchange contracts -- increased to 26.02
billion dollars from 25.93 billion dollars in the previous week,
The Jakarta Post Thursday quoted the report of the central bank as
saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
