<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Retail Sales Volume Rises Seven Percent In Four Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 27 (Xinhua)-- China's consumer goods retail sales
volume rose seven percent to 996.1 billion yuan during the first
four months of the year, according to a report from the State
Administration of Internal Trade.
</P>
<P>
In April, the country's consumer goods retail sales volume rose
5.7 percent to 235.7 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
In April, the sales of foodstuffs, clothing, interior
decoration materials, electronic audio-video products, and
telecommunications equipment rose between 11.4 percent and 163.2
percent.
</P>
<P>
Due to a price war, color TV sets, particularly 25 inch screen
models, chalked up a sales rate rise of 55.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Pork prices continued to drop in April by 23 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the first four months of the year capital goods sales volume
rose 7.5 percent to 1.21 trillion yuan.
</P>
<P>
In May, the report expects the social retail volume to rise 6.2
percent to 240.5 billion yuan, and the capital goods sales volume
will continue to rise at about eight percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
