<HEADLINE> Adams out of Euro 2000 Qualifiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Tony Adams will miss England's Euro
2000 soccer championship qualifiers against Sweden and Bulgaria
with a back injury.
</P>
<P>
His club Arsenal confirmed in a brief statement Wednesday that
Adams cannot be considered when England coach Kevin Keegan names
his squad on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"For the past two seasons Tony has experienced persistent
injuries," it said.
</P>
<P>
"On medical advice he has concluded that, in his current
physical condition and to help prevent any further aggravation of
the injury,a break during the summer would be in the best
interests of both England and Arsenal."
</P>
<P>
England face Sweden at Wembley next Saturday, then travel to
Bulgaria four days later. 
</P>
