<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Enters Semi-finals of Asian Club Basketball Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JUNIEH, Lebanon, May 26 (Xinhua) -- China's Liaoning club on
Wednesday defeated Saudi Arabia's Ittihad club in the 10th Asian
Basketball Confederation Champions Cup at the Ghazir Stadium in
Lebanon's central coastal city of Junieh.
</P>
<P>
The third consecutive victory sent Liaoning through to the semi-
finals as the group winner followed by Ittihad as the runner-up.
</P>
<P>
As the tournament favorite, Liaoning met with the strongest
challenge ever since the start of the tourney from Ittiahd, which
has at least three foreign stars.
</P>
<P>
However, with several consecutive three-pointers by Chinese
player Guo Jie in the second half, Liaoning coasted to a 87-78
victory in the end.
</P>
<P>
In previous games, Liaoning has beated Philippines' Pasig Rizal
Pirates club 97-66 and Kazakstan's CSCA club 86-71.
</P>
<P>
In another game of the day, Malaysia's Petronas club defeated
Jordan's Orthodox club 68-61, securing a semi-finals berth along
with Lebanon's Sagesse in the second group.
</P>
<P>
Semi-finals will be carried out on Friday with Liaoning against
Petronas and Ittihad against Sagesse.
</P>
<P>
The eight-day Asian Cup, which started on Saturday, features
club teams from China, Philippines, Kazakstan, Saudi Arabia, Japan,
Malaysia, Jordan, and Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
