<HEADLINE> Fujian's Private Economy Woos Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Privately-owned enterprises in
Fuzhou, the capital of east China's Fujian Province, have signed
32 cooperative contracts with overseas investors during the
ongoing month-long Fuzhou international investment fair.
</P>
<P>
The contracts involve an investment of 1.77 billion yuan, with
hi-tech projects worth 330 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Most of the projects offered by the private enterprises during
the fair cover the hi-tech, real estate, commerce and trade
sectors.
</P>
<P>
At present, there are 100,000 privately-owned industrial and
commercial enterprises in Fuzhou which employ 300,000 people.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the output value of these enterprises reached 3.5
billion yuan, with business turnover amounting to 1.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the city has 400 private enterprises engaging in
exports, and the annual export volume totaled 200 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
It was also reported that the Fuzhou Development Zone has
signed 25 agreements on using overseas funds totaling 150 million
U.S. dollars at the fair.
</P>
<P>
The contractual use of foreign investment totaled 130 million
dollars, sources from the provincial government said.
</P>
<P>
Thus, the number of overseas-funded projects in the development
zone, which includes an economic and technological development
zone, a zone for Taiwan investors, a hi-tech zone, a bonded zone
and an agricultural experiment zone for Taiwan investors, reached
733, involving 3.32 billion U.S. dollars in investment. The actual
use of foreign funds amounted to 840 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
