<HEADLINE> Measures Taken To Boost Hi-Tech Zone Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Jinan, capital of east China's
Shandong province, has been striving to create a favorable
environment for the improvement of its hi-tech development zone.
</P>
<P>
Efforts are used for improving infrastructure in the zone,
restructuring local outmoded enterprises with new technology,
granting the zone with more preferential policies and attracting
professionals to work there.
</P>
<P>
The Jinan Hi-Tech Development Zone has generated a combined 30
billion yuan worth of output value since it was set up in 1991.
</P>
<P>
The zone is now home to more than 2,500 enterprises, 240 of
which are in hi-tech areas and have developed as many as 378 hi-
tech products.
</P>
<P>
The number of enterprises each with more than 100 million yuan
of annual output value has reached 12 in the zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
