<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rocket in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Brazil's Sao Paulo
exchange, the largest in Latin America, closed up sharply
Wednesday with the benchmark Bovesa index surging by 6.06 percent
to 11,245 points, against 10,602 points Tuesday.
</P>
